-- IFC launches $2.5 bln rupee-denominated bonds for infra projects in India
-- By Manoj Kumar
-- Wed Aug 20, 2014 05:52AM EDT
-- None



NEW DELHI, Aug 20 (Reuters) - The World Bank's private-sector arm on Wednesday launched $2.5 billion, rupee-denominated bonds to fund infrastructure investments in India, the International Finance Corporation (IFC) said in a statement.

